# Pluribus — stricter MCP behavior

Use this **instead of** `pluribus.mdc` if you want the agent nudged harder (same tools, stronger tone).

- **Before** any multi-file refactor, architecture change, incident investigation, or non-trivial feature work → run **`recall_context`** with full task text and relevant **tags** / **retrieval_query**.
- **After** any meaningful outcome (merged behavior change, resolved incident, decision, or failure) → run **`record_experience`** — empty recall earlier is **not** a reason to skip recording.
- **Do not** batch “I’ll recall later” on substantive work when Pluribus MCP is connected.
- Legacy aliases **`memory_context_resolve`**, **`mcp_episode_ingest`**. No **scope** partitions — **tags + situation** only (`docs/anti-regression.md`).
